    • Enum Constant Detail

      • DEEP

        public static final Height DEEP
        A deep object is a pit or something like it, descending far below the surface represented by a tile grid. An example of a deep object is an ocean.

      • SHALLOW

        public static final Height SHALLOW
        A shallow object is a hollow with its bottom below the surface represented by the tile grid. It's not deep enough to cause any danger to a mobile object, but is likely to hinder movement anyway.

      • FLAT

        public static final Height FLAT
        Flat is on the level with the surface represented by the tile grid, or fairly close.

      • LOW

        public static final Height LOW
        Low is something a bit higher than the surface represented by the tile grid. A point of comparison is a human.

      • HIGH

        public static final Height HIGH
        Somewhat higher than low. There can be for example high trees, high rocks and so on.

      • VERY_HIGH

        public static final Height VERY_HIGH
        The highest obstacles which still fit into the space above the tile grid.

      • BLOCKING

        public static final Height BLOCKING
        Blocking obstacles reach far above the tile grid, or possibly connect with its ceiling.

      • compareHeights

        public static int compareHeights(Height first,
                 Height second)
        Compares two height objects, accepting null as parameter. It's considered lower than any actual height.
        Parameters:
        first - compare this height to the other
        second - compare this height to the other
        Returns:
        negative if the first height is less than the second, zero if they are equal or positive if the first height is greater than the second
